Action	                Command

Initialize repo	        git init
Add files	            git add .
Commit	                git commit -m "msg"
Push	                git push origin main
Pull                	git pull
Clone	                git clone <url>
Branch	                git branch feature
Switch	                git switch feature
Merge	                git merge feature
Status              	git status
Log	                    git log
Undo commit	            git reset

Check Git Version

Windows	        macOS	        Linux
git --version	git --version	git --version

Git Configuration (User Name & Email)

Same for all OS:

git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "email@example.com"

File System Commands (Different!)

Purpose	         Windows (Git Bash)	         macOS	         Linux

List files              	ls	              ls	           ls
Change directory	        cd	              cd               cd
Clear terminal	     clear or cls (CMD)	      clear	           clear
Remove file	            rm file.txt	       rm file.txt	    rm file.txt
Remove folder	        rm -rf folder	   rm -rf folder	rm -rf folder

SSH Key Generation

Task	                Windows	                    macOS	                           Linux

Create SSH Key	ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "email"	Same	                           Same
Copy SSH Key	clip < ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub	    pbcopy < ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub	   cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub

Line Ending Handling

OS	                         Default Setting

Windows	                     git config --global core.autocrlf true
macOS/Linux	                 git config --global core.autocrlf input